      • rentVehicle

        public int rentVehicle​(IEmployee employee,
                       int vehicleId)
                throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Tries to rent the vehicle for the specified employee. Notifies the employee to inform him/her of the rental result. Returns 0 if the vehicle can not be rent (for example, it has been sold during the rental process), 1 if the vehicle can be rent, 2 if the vehicle is already rent and the employee will be put on a waiting list
        Specified by:
        rentVehicle in interface IVehicleParkRentalManagement
        Parameters:
        vehicleId - the vehicle unique identifier
        employee - the employee who want to rent the vehicle.
        Returns:
        0 if the vehicle can not be rent, 1 if the vehicle can be rent or 2 if the vehicle is already rent and the employee will be put on a waiting list
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - may occur as this object will be used in remote method call.

      • returnCar

        public void returnCar​(int vehicleid,
                      int note,
                      java.lang.String conditionOfReturn)
               throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Called to return a car : add the note and condition of return to the vehicle and free it for next rental. If the waiting list of this car is not empty, rents the car to the first waiter and notifies him/her.
        Specified by:
        returnCar in interface IVehicleParkRentalManagement
        Parameters:
        vehicleid - the vehicle unique identifier
        note - the note given by the employee returning the vehicle.
        conditionOfReturn - a comment given by the employee to specify the condition of return of the vehicle.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - may occur as this object will be used in remote method call.
